textAnnotations.description:
The attached sketch was made by Capt. Cook, R.A.,
who was attached to the Force for sketching purposes.
The distances were obtained by measurement,
a bicycle wheel being used with a cyclometer
attached for this purpose.
The positions of camp were fixed by Mr. Sim,
Chief Officer in the British Steam Nav. Company ( lent
for Topographical purposes ). The latitude given
is in each case correct, but the longitude is
approximate only, owing to want of a sufficiently
reliable chronometer.
Gerelt madenial
Colonel.
Commanding. Ogeden Pun Force
Captain Cork w mfokmately too ite 5
compile a Oprah Whia he and otherwise

WOMAT. 89.
